headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 26 points, 18 rebounds and 16 assists for his 22nd triple-double of the season, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 130-101 on Sunday to clinch a playoff berth.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 26 points, 18 rebounds and 16 assists to lead Nuggets over Cavs, 130-101

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — LeBron James would only hint at how long he expects to keep playing NBA basketball.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James ties career high with 9 3-pointers, scores 40 points as Lakers beat Nets 116-104

headlines.description: — Paul George knocked down eight 3-pointers and finished with a season-high 41 points, and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated the Charlotte Hornets 130-118 on Sunday night for their fifth straight road win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul George pours in 41 points as Clippers continue dominance of Hornets with 130-118 victory

headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. scored a season-high 32 points, Kyle Lowry had 11 points and 10 assists against his former team and the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a three-game losing streak, beating the Toronto Raptors 135-120 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kelly Oubre Jr. scores season-high 32 points, 76ers beat Raptors 135-120 to end 3-game skid

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier III scored 27 points, Bam Adebayo had 22 and the Miami Heat grinded out a 119-107 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Adebayo help Heat outlast Wizards, move closer to sixth-place Indiana

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander made the go-ahead jumper from the corner with 2.6 seconds left, sending the Oklahoma City Thunder to the playoffs for the first time since 2020 with a 113-112 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder clinch first playoff spot since 2020, beat Knicks on Gilgeous-Alexander's jumper

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 47 points, 12 rebounds and seven assists, Kyrie Irving added 24 points and seven assists, and the Dallas Mavericks won their seventh straight and snapped the Houston Rockets’ 11-game winning streak with a 125-107 victory on Sunday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 47 as Mavericks win seventh straight and end Rockets' 11-game win streak

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 27 points and eight assists and Alex Caruso added 21 points on a season-high seven 3-pointers as the hot-shooting Chicago Bulls beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 109-101 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Caruso light it up as Bulls knock off Timberwolves 109-101

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 33 points and the Golden State Warriors held on to beat the undermanned San Antonio Spurs 117-113 on Sunday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 33 points, Warriors overcome Wembanyama, Spurs for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 24 points and keyed a big third-quarter run for Sacramento that carried the Kings to a 127-106 victory over the Utah Jazz on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harrison Barnes keys big 3rd quarter that carries the Kings past the Jazz 127-106
